
INSTALLMACRO
++++++++++++

SUMMARY
-------
Installs macro files in the global SAC macro directory.

SYNTAX
------

  ``INSTALLMACRO name {name ...}``

INPUT
-----
   :name:  The name of a SAC macro file.
    
DESCRIPTION
-----------
   This command lets you install your macro files into the global SAC macro
   directory so they can be used by anyone on your system. The location of this
   directory is defined by the SACAUX environmental variable, as SACAUX/macros.
   See the section on Macros in the SAC Users Manual.

SEE COMMANDS
------------
   MACRO_

LATEST REVISION
---------------
   March 20, 1992, (version 10.6e)

